# Slack Prototype Anatomy - Never Break These Rules

These are **non-negotiable structural constraints** for all Slack prototype screens. Violating these rules breaks the fundamental UI anatomy.

## 1. Header Positioning - Never Overlap or Hide

### Global Header
- **Height**: Exactly `40px` (CSS variable: `--header-height`)
- **Position**: `fixed`, `top: 0`, `z-index: 10000`
- **Visibility**: Always visible in prototype mode (never disappears, never fades)

### Slack App Header
- **Position**: Must render **below** the global header, never behind it
- **Offset**: Prototype container must have `padding-top: 40px` or `margin-top: 40px`
- **Z-index**: `z-index: 100` (below global header, above content)
- **Visibility**: Always rendered, never conditionally hidden based on view state

### Implementation Pattern
```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT: Prototype container offsets for global header
<div 
  className="prototype-screen"
  style={{ 
    paddingTop: 'var(--header-height, 40px)',
    height: 'calc(100vh - var(--header-height, 40px))'
  }}
>
  <div className="slack-shell">
    <AppHeader /> {/* Always first child, always visible */}
    {/* rest of content */}
  </div>
</div>

// ❌ WRONG: App header inside conditional render or view-specific component
{activeNav === 'dms' && <AppHeader />}
```

### Constraint
- App header must be a **direct child** of `slack-shell`, never inside `DemoSidebar`, `ActivityView`, `DMsView`, or any view-specific component
- Switching between DMs/Activity/Files/Later/Agentforce: **only** sidebar list content changes, app header never unmounts

---

## 2. Card Data Requirements - No Empty States Ever

### Rule
Every card that appears in any sidebar view (DMs, Activity, Files, Later, Agentforce) **must** have complete contextual dummy data. Empty cards are worse than absent cards.

### Required Data Fields

**Channel Card:**
- Channel name: `#deal-[accountname]` or `#[team]-[topic]`
- Preview text: Real sentence from fictional participant about fictional deal situation
- Timestamp: Realistic time (Today, 10:20 AM, Yesterday, etc.)
- Unread badge: Only if corresponding to actual unread messages

**DM Card:**
- Contact name: Named fictional person (first + last)
- Preview text: Last message in thread — complete, meaningful sentence
- Timestamp: Realistic
- Avatar: Person's initials or avatar — consistent across all arcs

**Activity Card:**
- Source: `#channel-name` or person name
- Action: Specific, readable action (replied, mentioned you, reacted)
- Preview: Actual message content being referenced
- Timestamp: Realistic

### Fictional Data Universe (Single Source of Truth)

**Contacts:**
```
Sarah Chen — Rita's manager
Priya Shah — Champion at Acme Corp ($180K deal)
Daniel Kim — VP Procurement at Acme Corp
Jordan Hayes — Contact at Greentech ($60K, closed)
Dana Torres — Contact at Runners Club
Marcus Lee — Former champion at Acme (departed)
Mike Torres — Contact at Sporty Nation
Lisa Park — Contact at TechStart
```

**Channels:**
```
#deal-acme       → Acme Corp $180K negotiation
#deal-greentech  → Greentech $60K (closed won)
#deal-runners    → Runners Club $55K at risk
#deal-sporty     → Sporty Nation $42K champion silent
#deal-techstart  → TechStart QBR prep
#q3-pipeline     → Internal pipeline review
#sales           → General sales team channel
#general         → Company general channel
```

### Implementation Pattern
```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT: Card has all required fields
<ActivityListItem
  item={{
    id: "deal-acme",
    name: "#deal-acme",
    preview: "Sent intro to Priya via Sarah. Daniel Kim — can we pull the...",
    timestamp: "Today",
    unread: true
  }}
/>

// ❌ WRONG: Missing preview or placeholder text
<ActivityListItem
  item={{
    id: "deal-acme",
    name: "#deal-acme",
    preview: "", // NEVER empty
    timestamp: ""
  }}
/>
```

### Constraint
- Cards without all three fields (name/channel, preview text, timestamp) must **not render** — hide entirely rather than show incomplete data
- Never use placeholder text: "No messages", "No data", "Loading...", or any placeholder
- Same person always has same name, same channel always has same deal context across all arcs

