## 4. Sidebar Structure - Never Break the Shell

### Rule
Sidebar has two zones. Both are structural and never re-render based on view state:

```
<SlackSidebar>
  <SidebarIconRail />     ← NEVER touches this. NEVER re-renders.
  <SidebarPanel>
    <SidebarHeader />     ← ALWAYS present. NEVER hidden.
    <SidebarList />       ← ONLY this zone changes when switching views
  </SidebarPanel>
</SlackSidebar>
```

### Constraint
- `<SidebarIconRail>` and `<SidebarHeader>` are **never** conditionally rendered
- Only `<SidebarList>` content swaps when switching Home/DMs/Activity/Files/Later
- Sidebar header (Direct messages title row) persists across ALL view changes

---

## 5. Presentation Mode Navigation

### Rule
In presentation mode (when `DesktopSlackShell` renders in `SceneLayout`):
- `workspaceId` param doesn't exist — always fallback to `"demo-1"`
- Navigation links must prevent default — update state only, don't navigate
- Content switches via `activeNav` state, not route changes

### Implementation Pattern
```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT: Fallback and prevent navigation in presentation mode
const workspaceId = (params.workspaceId as string) || "demo-1";
const { isPresentationMode } = usePresentationMode();

<Link
  href={href}
  onClick={(e) => {
    setActiveNav(item.id);
    if (isPresentationMode) {
      e.preventDefault(); // Don't navigate, just update state
    }
  }}
/>
```

---

## Checklist Before Any Change

Before modifying any Slack prototype code, verify:

- [ ] App header is visible and positioned below global header (not behind it)
- [ ] App header is not inside any view-specific component
- [ ] Every card in sidebar has: name, preview text, timestamp
- [ ] No placeholder text ("Loading...", "No data", etc.)
- [ ] Message input boxes in chat and Slackbot panel have identical padding (`px-3 py-2`)
- [ ] MessageInput component has no internal padding (parent controls it)
- [ ] Sidebar header never disappears when switching views
- [ ] In presentation mode, workspaceId falls back to "demo-1"
- [ ] Navigation prevented in presentation mode (state-only updates)

---

## Violation Examples

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG: App header inside conditional
{activeNav === 'dms' && <AppHeader />}

// ❌ WRONG: Empty card data
preview: "" // Missing preview text

// ❌ WRONG: Different padding
<div className="shrink-0 px-2 py-1"> {/* Different from px-3 py-2 */}
  <MessageInput />
</div>

// ❌ WRONG: Sidebar header conditionally rendered
{activeNav !== 'activity' && <SidebarHeader />}

// ❌ WRONG: No workspaceId fallback
const workspaceId = params.workspaceId; // undefined in presentation mode
```
